World-famous boxing champion, Anthony Joshua on Saturday got back his world heavyweight titles with a unanimous points win over Andy Ruiz Jr at the Diriyah Arena in Saudi Arena. In a bout earlier threatened by rain-storm, Joshua picked off a clear 118-110, 118-110, and 119-109 to defeated Ruiz Jr. in the highly anticipated fight. Ruiz shocked the boxing world when he stopped Joshua in seven rounds on June 1 in New York. But the latest victory has handed Joshua back his WBO, IBF, WBA belts that were taken from him following his defeat to Ruiz in their first fight. There was jubilation worldwide, especially in Africa following Joshua’s victory. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.